        I exclaim, "*SEVENTEEN!* This is the most organized adventure I've ever been on!"

        Scout bounces approvingly whenever I complete a section. Holloway coordinates everything with visible pleasure at our enthusiasm.

        Holloway says, "Submit when ready."

        I hit submit with a flourish.

        I say, "Filed! First inter-territorial travel request of my life!"

        Holloway says, "Travel request transmitted — response timeline... typically twenty-four to forty-eight hours."

        Two days of anticipation — I can handle that.

        ¶

        Approval comes eighteen hours later.

        I'm eating breakfast — mushroom paste, naturally — when Holloway's fruiting bodies sprout with unusual enthusiasm.

        Holloway says, "Excellent news! Your travel request has been approved! Guide assignments confirmed — territorial permissions secured!"

        I almost knock over my paste.

        I say, "Already?"

        Scout bounces so hard they roll off the table.

        Holloway says, "Expedited processing — exceptional circumstances! Your guides will arrive this afternoon. Departure: dawn tomorrow!"

        Tomorrow — *TOMORROW*.

        I shout to Buddy, "We're leaving *TOMORROW*!"

        Buddy says, "I heard! I'm already excited about the territorial boundary crossing procedures!"

        I ask, "Who are the guides? What are they like?"

        Holloway says, "Two guides for Territory One — Leafwhisper, excellent communication, very talkative — and Rootwalker, terrain specialist, quiet, direct. Contrasting styles!"

        Talkative guide and quiet guide — classic buddy-cop pairing.

        This is going to be amazing, I breathe.

        ¶

